                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Phelps</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 17, 1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 123.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 134 of the 30th ultimo,
                    relative to the refusal of Germany to alter the regulations for the exclusion of
                    American cattle, hogs, and hog products, has been received and confidentially
                    communicated to the Secretary of Agriculture for his information.</p>
                <p>The Department deeply regrets that Germany, in assigning reasons for her policy
                    of exclusion, has again taken the untenable ground that American meats are
                    unhealthful.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
